menu "breadboard: bb_cache_reactive"

config BB_CACHE_REACTIVE_ENABLE
    bool "Enable bb_cache_reactive change-driven observers"
    default n
    help
        When disabled, bb_cache_reactive_observe() compiles to a safe
        no-op (BB_ERR_UNSUPPORTED) and bb_cache_reactive_update() compiles
        to a direct passthrough to bb_cache_update() -- callers can invoke
        either unconditionally at zero cost. Disable on tight boards (e.g.
        ESP32-C3) that do not need change-driven push delivery.

        When enabled, observers registered via bb_cache_reactive_observe()
        are fired synchronously (on the writer's thread, after the
        internal observer-lock is released) whenever
        bb_cache_reactive_update() reports a changed value.

config BB_CACHE_REACTIVE_MAX_OBSERVERS
    int "Maximum number of registered reactive observers"
    default 8
    range 1 32
    depends on BB_CACHE_REACTIVE_ENABLE
    help
        Fixed-size observer pool. Each slot holds a key buffer
        (BB_CACHE_KEY_MAX bytes) plus three callback pointers and a ctx
        pointer -- cheap; raise only if more than 8 concurrent observers
        (e.g. WS delta sink + display + brood aggregator) are needed.

config BB_CACHE_REACTIVE_PAYLOAD_MAX
    int "Max serialized {ts_ms,data} envelope bytes fetched per on_change fire"
    default 512
    range 64 4096
    depends on BB_CACHE_REACTIVE_ENABLE
    help
        Stack buffer size used to fetch a changed key's serialized envelope
        via bb_cache_get_serialized() before firing on_change. Must be large
        enough to hold the largest observed key's envelope (512 matches the
        bb_net_health "net.health" precedent) or fire_on_change silently
        drops the notification (logged) for that key.

endmenu
